		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Iksar Shadow Knights, a rare breed ...<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Aug 1st 2:17 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=99668983961741&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=99668983961741&num=4&post=1&replyto=99668983961741"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=99668983961741></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=81196"><span id=>Shakeera</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>1 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.25]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Shakeera&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Just though I'd add my two cents worth about some of the posts I've seen here.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am a 45th level Iksar SK hunting fomr the Povar Server.<br><br>First off, it's VERY important that you keep ALL your melee skills trained as much as possible.  True, our epic is a 2hs and there's a lot of good swords out there.  But a really good SK will learn to use a skill depending on the situation.  If I'm gonna be the main tank in my goup (and this happens more often than I'd like) I use my Deathbringer's Rod at 30/40 to start; with haste items and spells, it does damage at a ratio of 30/30 or even lower at times.  Max hits of triple digits are common.  This weapon is a 2hb, and goes for about 4.5k on our server.  I LOVE it.  I plan to camp the Soulbinder soon - also a 2hb weapon.  Both of these weapons are worth training the skill for if you ever happen to land one.<br><br>One hand blunt is also a skill to practice if you like using a shield, because the Mace of the Shadowed Souls is about as good a one hand weapon as you can get.  Cheap too, runs about 3k on our server.  19/28 with +10int is awesome for a those that like seeing a good amount of battle spam on their screens, especially with haste items.  :)  I can hit with a MoSS for a max of 75-80 with about 135 str unbuffed.  Train with an Enameled Black Mace or an Ebonwood Cudgel (both can be bought under 800pp) early in levels so u can be ready for this weapon.<br><br>Then there is the Noctivagant Blade *shiver*  One hand slash, personally my favorite one handed weapon in the game.  Expensive to buy, but also worth training with.  Get a Yak at level 20 or so and use it to train your skill as you level up.<br><br><br>Now for strategy:  I love using my SK because we are an extremely diverse class to play.  I believe SKs are the second-best pullers in the game, bar none.  "Cast pulling" as I like to call it is not mana-draining, saves you from being hit and draws the mob in with aggro already built in.  Our debuff spells will draw the mob off enchanters while they are mesmerized as they do not break the mezz while being cast.  Contrary to what warriors say, we DO have the highest taunt abilities in the game, and contrary to what Paladins say we DO have the second highest HP and AC rates in the game  :)  As an Iksar I thought I would miss being able to wear Sentient or Darkforge armor...I love my full set of Rygorr at the moment and I look awesome in it.  Now that I am hunting in Velious I will be getting Skyshrine armor soon (prolly once I hit 52+).<br><br>Pets:  USE your pets!  Yes, they aren't mage pets or necro pets or even shaman pets.  BUT, they do two things.  One, they assist you automatically adding additional damae over time - hits of 15-25 over the course of the battle do add up!  And at higher levels the damage is even higher.  If a pet hits a mob for 150dmg over the entire battle that could mean the difference of whether you died or the mob did.  Secondly, by the time you get to lvl 40 or so you can accurately judge if you can win a battle or not.  So if you see that your puller has overdone himself, u can send a pet to fight something while either you finish off one mob or run to the zone.  My pet can usually keep a mob busy for 7 to 10 seconds, which we all know can be an eternity when it comes to getting of a heal, a nuke, finishing a mob or running for a zone line.<br><br>Hunting Zones:<br><br>I won't tell you where to hunt up to level 20.  Most hunting areas close to the cities you start in provide you with enough battle areas to get you to lvl 20.<br><br>From 20 on, here is where I have made my exp and money in Kunark:<br><br>20-25:  I hunted in the Sarnak Fortess at the Lake of Ill Omen.  from 20-22 I hunted the front door area and from 23-25 I went to the back door to kill adherants and revenants.  Get a good group and watch your pet closely, trains can become unmanageable.<br><br>25-30:  I hunted the giant fortress at the Frontier Mountains.  Decent exp, good place to make 100pp in about 2 hours.  If you feel really brave u can hunt the sarnak or goblin camps around the area as well, but the chances for wandering mobs and getting lost are much higher.<br><br>30-38:  The Overthere is the most awesome place to gain exp I know yet.  Tons of mobs, easy access to a zone, and a good place to find a group.  Kill anything red, blue or yellow with a good group and you will level fast.  You can also try Iceclad Ocean and the Eastern Wastes in Velious, I was there for a couple of levels but returned to the Overthere.<br><br>39-present:  I am dividing my time between Lower Guk, the Dreadlands, and the Great Divide in Velious.  Better loot in Velious, and u can raide factions there easily.  Dreadlands is closest to home of course, and in Lower Guk u can get awesome loot but it's crowded and getting a group can be a pain when there's 50 people in the zone and only 6 camps available.  I plan to to hunt in the City of Mist from levels 46-50, great loot and exp there.<br><br>After lvl 50 I am gonna try Karnor's and Chardok in Kunark, and Velketor's Labrynth in Velious.  I have usually stayed away from Antonica and Faydwer except when I need to auction stuff (like the weird folks we are, Povar users do their auctioning and business in Greater Faydark - don't ask me why).<br><br>Anyway, there is a bit of a strategy guide for u Iksars out there that dream of becoming like me LOL (just kidding).  Remember that you are evil, and you will always be evil.  Use it to your advantage.<br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Shakeera Serpiente<br>Iksar Shadow Knight<br>Risen Phoenix Guild Officer<br>Povar Server</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
