		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.09]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=lunaticfringesk&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Nice read.<br><br>Not sure I agree with everything you stated, but, as I am an IKS SHD myself, I smiled nonetheless with the stroll down memory lane (or was it amnesia lane--heck, I can't remember)<br><br>Re: melee skills--I would just put your best weapon in your hand and go to town rather then worry about maxxing each melee skill at each level (or something similar).&nbsp;&nbsp;At most, switching between a 1H and shield vs. a higher DPS 2H might be a switch considering the situation, but I personally wouldn't sweat melee skills.  They rise real fast later on.  /shrug--have fun if ya want though.<br><br>Shard of Night is a 1HP that I would definitely consider looking into for a (hopefully--it's SHD only) cheap option that wasn't mentioned.  It's also much better then MoSS, Noc Blade, and *can* do more DPS then MDS (at higher levels).  Further, at lower levels, it would be better then MDS (until the damage caps come off).<br><br>Agree that SHD are *not* the 2nd best pullers in the game (in general).  Classes with pacify can be better as well at times.  It's kinda a situational thing, but SHD are seldom the best or even 2nd best puller.<br><br>I think you are mixing up the term &quot;taunt&quot; with &quot;agro.&quot;  SHD do *not* have the best taunt in the game--WAR do.  It's fact; they have higher taunt cap.  <br><br>SHD *can* have better agro then a WAR, but that fades fast in the end game and SHD/PAL actually have less agro over time then a WAR does (it's pathetic what WAR can do in the endgame as far as agro goes).<br><br>Not sure what you are basing the comment that SHD have the 2nd highest HP and AC rates in the game.  That isn't true, all things equal.<br><br>Re: pets--assisting you automatically is *not* a good thing all the time.  If you disagree, ask yourself why the AA *pet hold* was created (and the answer isn't pulling, but a cool trick nonetheless /grin)<br><br>I would also strongly consider adding some Luclin and LoY maps to your hunting grounds as well.  <br><br>In any case, have fun with your IKS SHD.  IKS advantage pretty much lies in *one* area---the AC bonus.  Enjoy it.  /grin<br><br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=560565" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=560565</a><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=99668983961741&num=4&post=1&mid=99668983961741><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">4 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class5">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
